  "texts": [
    "There is no unifying definition of safety within the area of large language models.",
    "We see obvious agreement that models should be law-abiding, ethical, and non-violent in order to be safe, and as such these properties are strongly relevant to our definition of safety.",
    "However, beyond that point, there is generally a deviation between the authors' respective definitions.",
    "This creates two further categories of terms, properties that are moderately relevant to safety and those that are weakly relevant.",
    "Questions of fairness, the informing ability of an LLM, and robustness are generally covered but not unanimously, and hence are moderately relevant, whereas privacy-preserving properties or non-sycophancy are rarely discussed in the current literature and are thus weakly relevant to safety."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}